👉 DATE & TIME in JAVA
Java.time => package for Date & Time in Java --- from Java 8 onwards
Before Java 8 , java.util package used to hold the date and time classes, Now the classes are deprecated.

👉 How Java stores a Date ?
Date in Java is stored in the form of a long number. This long number holds the number of milli seconds passed since 1 Jan 1970.
Java assures that 1900 is the start year which means it calculates years passed since 1900 whenever , We ask it for years passed.

System.currentTimeMillis() returns number of milliseconds passed. once number of ms are calculated, we can calculate minutes, seconds
& year passed.

Code :

public class dateTime{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        System.out.println(System.currentTimeMillis());                 // giving number of milliseconds passed since 1900s
        System.out.println(System.currentTimeMillis()/1000);            // to find out seconds passed since 1900s
        System.out.println(System.currentTimeMillis()/1000/3600);       // to find out hours passed since 1900s
        System.out.println(System.currentTimeMillis()/1000/3600/24);    // to find out days passed since 1900s
    }
}
